name: Mount Rainier National Park Day Trip and Private Tour
description: Day trip tour of all the best scenic sites throughout Mount Rainier National Park and surrounding area. Small group size of 4 or less for a more intimate, customized experience. We offer a premium catered lunch made of fresh, local ingredients. Also have a variety of snacks and specialty beverages available for your choosing. Knowledgeable and friendly NW native tour guide to show you around and teach you about this majestic wilderness through short nature hikes and/or snow activities tailored to your group. We will see and learn about the different ecosystems, wildlife, and geological history of the park, while also admiring and respecting its rugged, natural beauty. Endless photo opportunities will be available for you to capture this memorable day. Safe and reliable transportation provided by a 4x4 Toyota 4-Runner SUV and a guide with over 20 years of professional driving experience.

itemListElement.name: Self Guided 'Trolling for Treasures in Fremont' Solo Walking Tours

name: Self Guided 'Trolling for Treasures in Fremont' Solo Walking Tours
description:
Explore Fremont! Seattle's Funkiest hood! Go at your own pace and on your schedule on this unique one of a kind tour of Fremont AKA that Center of the Universe. 

On this funky tour of Fremont, Seattle, I’ll be navigating you to all that is uniquely Fremont, the center of the universe. Yes, you heard right, as declared by Kings County, Fremont is the center of the Universe, and you’ll see the sign to prove it. On this solo tour for travel rebels, you’ll see what makes Fremont funky, including the Fremont Rocket, the largest Lenin statue you may have ever seen, a giant troll that lives under a bridge, local statues, the Berlin wall, dinosaurs and you’ll even stop by an operating chocolate factory, how about that. So why don’t you get your cute butt down to the Fremont Troll. That’s where the tour starts. I’ll meet you there.

review.name: Troll surprise!
review.reviewBody:
We had no idea what we were going to see as we hadn’t seen any pictures prior, which made the experience more fun when we spotted the colossus underneath the bridge.
Enjoyed the troll and the sights around Fremont, the vintage shop is one of the best stocked of its kind and the  walk back to the city along the lake was enjoyable too.

review.name: App wouldn't download
review.reviewBody: We weren't able to listen to this because the app would not download.  I also realized it was quite a distance from our hotel and the Lyft to get there would have been pricey but I would have still like to listen to the info.  I clicked the link to cancel and the fee to cancel was the full price of the tour.

name: Leavenworth Exclusive Tour from Seattle
description:
This tour is all things that you expected to see in just one day. It will be full of unbelievable beauty of nature. 
Also, we will stop at the bigfoot watching area. you would take some memorable pictures with bigfoot on Espresso Chalet. 
How could be all this beauty in one package? You will see. 
[German town – Leavenworth] is the most famous German town in the northwest of the United States. On arrival in the Bavarian town (Leavenworth), you’ll have two hours for lunch (own expense) with free time to explore. The German town - Leavenworth has more than 90 shops, each with a unique style including wine shops and art galleries. There are also many restaurants operating German-style cuisines, such as the German village of Schweinshaxe, German sausage, and Munich beer, which has won the tourists' favor.

review.name: Leavenworth- worth the visit
review.reviewBody:
I recently visited Leavenworth, a charming town about 125 miles east of Seattle, which offers a delightful blend of German food and culture. What made this weekend getaway truly unforgettable was the scenic journey. The drive presented breathtaking views of nature, with the river flowing beside us for a long stretch, and in some spots, snow-capped mountains towering just next to the road. It was an experience that stole my heart, making the trip as memorable as the destination.

Comment here for information on this whole trip to Leavenworth.

review.name: Quaint Bavarian Village
review.reviewBody: Long, scenic ride with plenty of restroom breaks.  Two hours plenty of time to eat lunch but if you like to shop,  probably need more time. Our guide, Farshid, was a friendly and safe driver.

review.name: Great trip !
review.reviewBody: Farshid our guide was amazing and super attentive ! He was able to accommodate us to the max since it was our first time in Seattle and we really enjoyed the drive and stops along the way ! Great hospitality and would definitely book again with them .. thank you so much for the memories !

review.name: EXCELLENT TOUR TO LEAVENWORTH
review.reviewBody: It was an excellent tour which I'd highly recommend to everybody. I was picked up at the hotel around 9:30 am and was dropped off around 6 pm. Water and snacks were provided. Van was comfortable, driver/tour guide Farshid was very nice: responsible and knowledgeable and an awesome driver. 3,5 hrs from Seattle to Leavenworth with several stops, including Big Foot coffee shop, Tumwater Dam, Eagle Falls on Skykomish river, Deception Falls. Tumwater Dam on Wenatchee river. Then we had 2 hours in Leavenworth, where you can buy souvenirs in multiple souvenir shops, and dine Bavarian style food. Suggestion: first eat, then shop, as there are lines to get to some restaurants. Horse ride is expensive but seems like everyone was enjoying it. On the way back to Seattle we stopped at Stevens Pass ski resort. It was a fay full of impressions, no regret or disappointment at all. I'd go there in summer time as well, however I think there are way too many tourists in summer time and you won't be able to enjoy tranquility of nature.

review.name: Amazing day trip to Leavenworth!
review.reviewBody:
We had an amazing day on our trip to Leavenworth. Our guide was Slav. He was kind enough to pick us from our place. We were given snacks and water at the beginning of the tour. He also played trivia on the way which was very fun and interesting. We made stops in Index ( coffee shop) , ski resort, Leavenworth and Deception pass. Our guide was amazing and waited for everyone, no rush! We had a wonderful time in Leavenworth (around 2.5hrs), explored the place at our own pace .On our way back we had a small hike to Deception fall, it’s a beautiful hike with most amazing waterfall views. 
Slav offered to take pictures of everyone. Thank you so much ! We really enjoyed a lot with the group. I highly recommend taking this tour.

review.name: Highly Recommend it
review.reviewBody: Booked a day tour to Leavensworth  and Stevens Pass from Seattle.. the tour was comfortable,fun and beautiful places... Mr Slav was very friendly and loved the experience.. Highly recommend it !!

review.name: Amazing tour!
review.reviewBody: The tour guide Mehrdad was extremely sweet and took great care of us! The entire trip was very nice and the views were also amazing. Would highly recommend!

review.name: Leavenworth during Christmas
review.reviewBody: Great tour and Leavenworth is beautiful in December. The stops on the way were great and the amount of time in town was just the right amount.

review.name: Trip to Leavenworth
review.reviewBody:
My visit to Leavenworth was an enjoyable and memorable experience. However, I did feel that the allotted time to explore the town was too short. With only two hours, it felt more like 30 minutes, especially as a first-time visitor eager to take in everything the town has to offer.

That said, our driver, Mehrdad, truly enhanced the experience. He was fantastic, sharing engaging and informative facts about the surroundings throughout the journey. Additionally, the scenic pit stops he included allowed us to capture stunning photos, which was a great touch.

Overall, I would rate this experience a 7/10. The only improvement I’d suggest is extending the time spent at the destination to allow for a more immersive visit.

review.name: The perfect Christmas town & the courtesy of the driver Slav
review.reviewBody: Our driver,Slav set the tone for our trip with his professional,kind,cheerful,& humorous  spirit.the trip was everything I could have imagined.beautiful & breathtaking.i will do this one day your next time i come.

itemListElement.name: Four Seattle Breweries, and crazy history

name: Four Seattle Breweries, and crazy history
description: We'll go to 4 of the best breweries in Seattle. The first one has the only museum of beer and brewing on the Pacific Coast, another one is the most haunted location in Seattle, yet another one makes the best beer in the city, in our opinion. You'll hear fascination stories not only from Seattle's scandalous past (prostitution, murder, mayhem, the failures of the underground), but also ghost stories, and the world history of beer.

review.name: Lots of fun!
review.reviewBody: My brother and I took our 82 year old dad for his birthday. He loves a good IPA. Had a terrific time! Our tour guide was full of good stories that even us locals hadn’t heard before. He was smart and funny and we thoroughly enjoyed every minute. The breweries were new to us as well. The other people on the tour were also a lot of fun. We made a great memory for dad and he wants to do it again next year. Maybe a new tradition?

itemListElement.name: Seattle Plant Nite Crafts Event by Yaymaker

name: Seattle Plant Nite Crafts Event by Yaymaker
description:
Dig Into a Creative Succulent Party with Plant Nite. Plants. Gotta love ‘em! They can really change the mood of a room. They brighten up spirits with their ability to freshen the air and provide some serious de-stressing vibes. At Yaymaker, we love the idea of getting people together to laugh, share a drink and try a new activity.

Plant Nite experience is a lot like our other experiences, with a dash of dirt to keep things interesting. You’ll visit a nearby bar or restaurant where a local host will be your guide for two hours of terrarium making fun. You’ll have just as much fun as you would at an Original Paint Nite event (drinks and friends, check!). Instead of heading home with a beautiful canvas, you’ll be digging into a fun-filled plant design experience.

name: Private Transportation to the Boeing Factory Tour from Seattle
description:
Experience private round-trip transportation from Seattle to the Boeing Future of Flight & Factory Tour, located 45 minutes north of the city. Tickets into the Factory Tour should be added in the checkout process. 
Your tour begins from your Seattle hotel, where you'll be greeted by your tour guide and whisked away on a flight enthusiasts dream. During the 45 minute drive, your guide will lay the groundwork for you, providing a brief history of The Boeing Company along with what to expect when you arrive. 

Time allowed for the Future of Flight Gallery, the SkyDeck, 80-minute public Boeing Factory Tour and giftshop. The option to add additional time is available on a case-by-case basis. 

It is important to note that your tour at the Boeing Factory will not be private - your transportation will be.

review.name: it was wonderful !!
review.reviewBody: thank you Eugene Ford the concierge for sending me to the factory of Boeing make sure northwest tours tip him he knows where to send his guest.

name: Morning-Private boat salmon charter
description: Most salmon charters in the Seattle area use a heavy gear and down riggers. While effective we believe a better experience is Salmon Mooching. This technique uses lighter gear and allows the angler to work the bait and feel the exiting take of a Puget Sound Salmon. Its the best way to fish Seattle!

review.name: Best Salmon fishing experience on the Puget Sound.
review.reviewBody:
The ONLY salmon guide you will want to consider fishing the Puget Sound with. Took my dad and I out for a AM charter, which was a breeze to book even for my 70 year old father. Dave welcomes any and all (Fishers, non-fishers, seattle-ites and out of towners alike).

Cap't Dave was easily accessible by phone to answer all questions personably and professionally.  He was on-time at the dock with a friendly smile and quick to get us out on the water. 

The depth of knowledge Dave has as a fisherman and a captain combined can not be compared to other charters. The boat a high quality gradywhite which is clean, quiet, and smooth. From the moment we got on the water we were put on fish. 

The method was simple and even a non-fishing person would have a great day out on the boat. Dave has everything covered from rain gear, bait, and tackle.  The best part of the day was when we hooked up and caught a triple, 3 salmon at once. 

Those kind of experiences and moments do not happen on every charter. We will be back and I'd strongly urge you to look no further and just book Wind Knot with Cap't Dave.

name: Uncover Seattle: Self-Guided Audio Tour
description:
Seattle is a hidden gem among the cities of America and is well worth a visit. Birthplace of Starbucks and home to a dazzling array of seafood, Seattle is a foodie’s paradise.
Seattle is not just a destination for food-lovers. The city is home to an array of landmarks and stunning views providing something new to see at every turn. This self guided audio tour is the perfect way to experience it all in your own time and at your own pace.
The tour is expertly written by travelling researcher, past editor-in-chief and author Maurice J. Gallagher. Maurice’s writing is superbly narrated by voice artist Linda Browne whose velvet-like voice is a popular feature of many of our city audio tours. Linda will expertly guide you through the city uncovering its history and quirks along the way.
Simply download the self-guided audio tour, plug in your headphones, open the map that comes with your download and head to the tour starting point. 
Please note this tour is only available in English.

review.name: Not worth the money
review.reviewBody: I have used audio driving tours for several years. This one unfortunately was the worst one I have experienced. It was difficult to use, the logic of how the points were mapped out didn’t make sense and the navigation wasn’t included in the audio. I won’t be using this company again.

review.name: Kind of boring compared to a human tour guide￼
review.reviewBody: I did not enjoy this at all, but if you were looking for a way to get information about the city on the cheap, it may work for you.￼

review.name: Really amazing
review.reviewBody: Enjoyed the tour and the ability to spend time at more places due to quiet Covid times but we shot back to the free hotel wife to download so we didn't end up with Roaming charges. Good information and easy to work. Recommend.

review.name: Great Tour
review.reviewBody: Seattle is a beautiful city made even better when you walk around on your own with the audio guide. No noisy distractions. Enjoyable morning.

review.name: What happened?
review.reviewBody: We booked this through Viator.  Our travel agent confirmed it the night before.  Had to find out where we needed to be - at the Marriott Hotel2100 Alaskan Way, since we were staying outside the pick-up area.  We were told to be there by 9:30 and look for somebody with the Viator sign.  We were there by 9:20.  By 9:45, we saw nobody with a Viator sign so I called.  Was on phone at least a half hour.  Was told we had not confirmed.  That was done last evening.  Was also told we could take tour for another $110.  Are you kidding us?  After much frustration and repeating SEVERAL times, "give me a refund", she finally said our credit card would show a credit in 3 to 5 days.  It's been 4 days and we are still waiting to see the credit.  DO NOT BOOK THIS TOUR.

name: Private Catamaran Charter
description:
On a typical 4 hr charter, Amelia departs Shilshole Marina and heads SW past West Point Lighthouse. Clearing the point, we encounter spectacular views of Rainier and sea lions perched on channel markers. Heading further S, we take in the majestic Olympic and Cascade mountains, and watch the ferries shuttle passengers between Bainbridge Island and downtown Seattle. We then sail into Elliott Bay, for an up close look at Seattle's incredible waterfront before turning back N towards Bainbridge Island and finally Shilshole Marina.

With 5 or more hrs, we can sail you and your party around Bainbridge Island, through sublime Agate Passage.

With 6 or more hrs, we sail to serene Port Madison or sun soaked Blake Island, where we anchor out, kayak, swim, explore the shoreline. Alternately, we can sail into the artsy town of Winslow, Bainbridge Island, for lunch or dinner before heading back to Seattle (note: all longer charter cover standard 4 hr charter agenda, plus the additional items noted).

review.name: Best way to spend a day in Seattle!
review.reviewBody: What a beautiful boat and trip.  As a first time sailer the captain combined a perfect blend of fun and education.  For anyone wanting to go out on the sea around Seattle, have an amazing time and learn more about how to sail with Amelia Catamaran Charters!

review.name: Great experience!
review.reviewBody: I celebrated my birthday on Amelia charters and had a fantastic time! We sailed out and saw breathtaking views of Puget Sound and mountains in the distance. Aside from the amazing sailing experience, the crew was fun, accommodating, and maintained an excited energy the entire trip that made us feel comfortable and welcome.

review.name: Amazing Seattle cruise
review.reviewBody: Great time on the cruise! It was fun for the whole family. He had a float for the young adults to sit on on the water and enjoy the swim! I highly recommend Amilia Catamaran Charters!

review.name: Stunning Scenic view of the Puget Sound and Olympic Mountains
review.reviewBody: Sailing with Li at Amelia Catamaran was a wonderful experience! The fresh air, sunshine and spectacular view of the PNW Mountains will stay with me for years to come. I highly recommend Amelia Catamaran Charter to visitors and locals alike!

review.name: The best way to see the water in beautiful Seattle!
review.reviewBody: I'm about to reserve another charter for my next vacation in Seattle.  Everything was just perfect and so easy!  Amelia Catamaran Charters makes your trip extra special, and the price was very reasonable.  I recommend getting a taste of the boating life on Amelia Catamarans.

review.name: Amazing day trip with a great guide. Highly recommended.
review.reviewBody:
Only had little time in Seattle and definitely wanted to see the Great Outdoors.

Messaged Sophia via her homepage and she replied in no time with all the required information.

She picked me up on Saturday morning, on time, with a coffee, a croissant and some fruits waiting in the car for breakfast.

Sophia drives super safe and the views along the road up to the Three Burroughs Hike are stunning. 

The group (Sophia and us 2 "customers" + her bf and one visting friend) was great fun - it feels more like a day out with likeminded people and there was never any boring time during the whole trip- you can easily feel that Sophia truly enjoys doing those hikes.

Sophia provided poles, a backpack, water, sun screen, snacks, etc. 

The food for lunch was delicious and plentiful, the route interesting, lots of good conversation and an amazing scenery.

If you are in Seattle and you want to get outdoors for a day or two, I would definitely recommedn to go with Sophia. She also offers motorbike tours and horseback tours.
